cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper deals with computer vision and deep learning techniques to solve the problem of Non-Rigid Structure from Motion (NRSfM). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel hierarchical sparse coding model for NRSfM, which involves training an unsupervised deep neural network (DNN) auto-encoder. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of modern deep learning computational platforms, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new quality measure based on network weights, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
